I imagine there is a lot of oblique crossover there. Similar issues, different physiology, etc. Ultimately for me it always comes back to quality of life. My desire to keep him forever is not compelling if he’s in constant, unmanageable pain.
@fartsock @MaeNena73 @sasshole @mac_b5 Added to my list!

@mac_b5 When I worked at the vet in college, we had a deaf dog who boarded frequently and had a whole sheet of visual commands. It’s the gradual loss that’s new to me. @madstatler also suggested clapping, so that may be our first step too
@AK_Chick Noted! Pellet-form first!

@MariePaddock I’ve had older dogs before, but it was before I was in charge of them and ultimately my job was to feed them and to love them and play with them. I was present at many vet visits, but the decisions weren’t mine. Brady is the first dog who is truly *mine* so it all feels different
@AK_Chick I do ☺️ and I’m really grateful I knew exactly who to ask!

@fartsock @MaeNena73 @sasshole @mac_b5 I have never heard of a dog-safe ibuprofen and now I’m intrigued!

We do what we can on all the other points, especially weight as Brady gets older and given his spinal issues. Thanks, Jess!
@jorleigh1 @AK_Chick This was exactly my point at the time—we don’t know until we check. And since it isn’t *that* invasive, I would rather check and be wrong than find out too late.
@AK_Chick @jorleigh1 Honestly I think being out of Chicago will help.
@mackaracka Wow, you have a ton of experience! It sounds like you found ways to make it very manageable, too. If it’s okay, I may hit up up with questions along the way.

@BirdNerdSarah @AK_Chick Another vote in favor of acupuncture Thankfully Brady’s isn’t reactive at all (except the barking). That may end up being a bigger problem down the road with Fred, but thankfully that is many years off.

@thegirlpurls Thank you so much Lori! ❤️ It’s heartening to hear that these are more common than I originally thought. Even so, when all of a sudden you’re feeling lumps, it’s pretty scary, so I’m glad I’m not off base to be concerned, just to dial it back to awareness-level.

@BirdNerdSarah @mac_b5 Right? At 65-68ish, Brady is the lightest of our Trio. The help em up harness that a few people have mentioned looks promising for what I need, but a ramp may also be something we explore.
@MariePaddock Sounds like I will be hitting you up for insights as we go, though! 😁

@MariePaddock Poor buddies! I’m so glad that Dynamo can still get to do walks and enjoy them with those interventions! With B we are still okay reserving gabapentin for really bad spine days,  so right now this is as much about prevention and extending quality of life as it is preparing.

@thesusan We have a similar anxiety treatment for Fred for really hard days. Thankfully Brady is mostly okay right now, but I do wonder as he gets older. I will keep these suggestions in mind, thanks! Hope your buddy is doing well!

@the_rbf HOLY COW😱

Thank you for sharing that! What an improvement! She looks like such a sweetheart, too. Okay, definitely looking at the things you suggested now!

@the_rbf All the votes in favor of hydrotherapy are seriously helping me with this decision. Thank you! Harness is now in the cart, to be ordered on Friday lol.

I’m going to check out my options for a chiropractic vet practice and see what I can find. Thanks for that tip!

@AK_Chick Originally we were doing raw, but when I got laid off that became difficult to maintain and the dogs didn’t love it. So now we do dry raw-coated kibble in the morning, and kibble plus 8oz of raw in the evening. It lets us vary when they get bored and seems to satisfy them more.

@AK_Chick I’ve had a couple biopsied because they were both growing and multiplying, but honestly the attitude of the vet was that I was overreacting when *clearly* they were benign. We haven’t found a new vet here in WI yet, but it will be a priority when we do.
@AK_Chick This one is harder to find close by, but also one to keep in the back pocket!

@AK_Chick Definitely going to check this out. They *hate* the supplements they’re on now, which is why we tried cbd to begin with. I see this comes in stinky treat and liquid varieties both, so it might be a winner with the Divas.
@madstatler All the stories you’ve told me about Murph have convinced me that she was as much an utter sweetheart as you are, and that you were truly meant for eachother ❤️
@MeganJBradley @jorleigh1 That sounds like a plan I’m going to keep in my back pocket for sure. Thanks! ❤️
@madstatler Noted and to be shortly added to cart!
@madstatler I may be texting you about some of this later if that’s okay ❤️
@jorleigh1 Another heavy vote in favor of the water therapy. This is so helpful, seriously. Thank you so much!

@madstatler I’ve been thinking about this too. Also more one-on-one time with the old man, since he doesn’t get nearly enough of that these days; especially since Beau has discovered the fun of car rides

@jorleigh1 😱that is MASSIVE. Poor thing!

I will say the thing that saves me is that I’ve seen them before with labs and some GSD mixes (which Brady is), but yeah the size and location of this one are the big concern for me.

@madstatler I may have to try this—and get Fred acclimated so anxiety pup doesn’t have a heart attack at the loud noises 😂

He’s not too bad yet, but I have been noticing more that he isn’t hearing things, so this sounds like a really solid approach. Thank you ❤️
@jorleigh1 Thank you so much ❤️ so affirming, because this is what we have been doing, and reinforces that I’m not crazy to be keeping a close eye.

@jorleigh1 We have used gabapentin in the past on days when the other measures don’t work for him, or after he’s been bodyslammed by the other 2. It makes him dopey but does seem to help. Sounds like the water therapy is going to be our best choice for next modality to try. Thanks!
@jorleigh1 Thank you so much for your thoughts! I didn’t think there would be much for the startling lol but it was worth a shot.

@jorleigh1 Thank you ❤️ the one that concerns me the most is about 4” across & subcutaneous, right under one leg over his lungs. We’re in-between vets atm so that is on the list to have checked out, but this does make me feel better about the others (all pretty small and other places)
RT @BooksHonest: Tonight!!! Note the 6pm start time. Kate is staying up late to speak to us from London.

Also if anybody with shepherd/GSD/husky experience knows anything about benign lipomas and can share some insights, it would be appreciated. They scare me and while the vet insists they aren’t an issue, I worry about them putting pressure on nerves and that they keep multiplying

He is fairly well-trained with non-verbal commands, but he startles more than he used to; and when he startles he startles LOUD, which gets the other two going. Nobody loves this, but it does seem somewhat unavoidable at this point.

For example, disintegrating disc disease is something we’ve been facing for several years now. Supplementation works to a point, and CBD makes him more comfy. We’re considering water therapy at a place in Oshkosh, but am open to other ideas.

To be clear, am categorically NOT contemplating pet loss or anything like it rn!

Genuinely interested in the canine equivalent of aging in place strategies for larger dogs

Sir Brady is 11 this year and as is true of most of us when you achieve a certain age, the miles are starting to show. How have y’all adjusted to deal with things like hearing loss and mobility issues?

Next tweet is going to be a random question that is not intended to be triggering at all re:aging pets. Will be threaded, so you can choose to miss it if this isn’t something you have spoons for.

And that is how we met our neighbors, some guy named Bob, got some free corn, and potentially found a couple of dogsitters for our Motley Crue, just by mentioning that we were looking for a thing.

Turns out we have neighbors over the hill with a 14 year old and a 16 year old who love animals and would be very interested.

By the way, we should come and get some sweet corn before it goes for the season.

So Tom asked Bob (who I don’t actually know but apparently knows the previous owners and has lived here forever too), and Bob asked somebody else, and I look out my window today and there’s an ATV I don’t recognize in my driveway and the doorbell is ringing.

So we asked Tom if he could recommend anybody in the area who would be interested in a paid intermittent house/dog sitting gig. It requires getting to know the dogs first (looking at you, Fred), and coming by now and again so they are comfortable and familiar with whoever we get.

Tom is a friend of the family that owned this property for generations. He grew up hunting in the woods out back and has been incredibly kind to us since we moved in. He and his wife made us walleye when they had a fish fry, and they even shared some of their venison last season.

Except one guy.

So do not think that these FI’s demarketing Trump, his businesses, or his extended family is a reflection of their commitment to any particular political stance or doing what’s right.

They are protecting themselves against the optics of being the bank of Trump. That’s it.

/fin

A friend asked me once if we based our decisions on whether banking somebody made the bank look good or not.

The truth is that yeah; we often did.

Our job wasn’t to serve humanity at large or society; our job was to protect the bank. That’s it.

In my previous roles, we made this choice, over and over again. Yes, there are processes in place prior to closure and there are review processes after the recommendation is made, but it often comes down to judgment made by a single investigator.

A customer who is borderline by other lenses of evaluation can (and often is, depending on a given FI) be demarketed purely given the degree of reputational risk they pose the institution if the relationship is made public.

Risk is evaluated in multiple contexts: risk presented by their activities, their business relationships, their personal relationships and standing. Exposure to legal outcomes is always considered, but a key component of the risk calculation is reputational risk posed to the FI
But several intangibles are also taken into account, particularly (and this is true of every FI I’ve ever worked at) the risk presented by a given customer.

In a closure review, multiple factors are considered: current activity, historical activity, relationships, and political exposure chief among them. 

Financial institutions have a responsibility to ensure that their customers who are compliant with state, fed, and int’l AML regs

Do not think for a second that this is an altruistic move. 

This is not recognition of his deeds as a bad actor, this is not in regards to him as a person. Banks can and do make a ton of money off people like Trump.

This is about risk.

So I’m seeing a lot of people talking about financial institutions that are divesting themselves of their relationships with Trump, esp. re: his personal accounts.

Also I have to build two 6-foot gates.
Because it’s supposed to snow on Saturday.

It’s going to be a hell of a lot colder tomorrow (our high is supposed to be almost 20* lower than today’s was), and I will have to set 34 posts, ten of which I still need to move into position...

...and then load, ferry, and re-unload 2560 lbs of concrete mix.
I only managed to set six of them before I lost the light.

So dammit, I loaded, hauled, and unloaded over 5000lbs of concrete today, then loaded and moved 30 posts (To do the two far legs of the fence), and placed all of those suckers adjacent to their future homes.

As a consequence, I spent twice as long as I needed too and zapped my oomph WAY faster than I should have.

I have a recurrent back injury that, when activated, renders me incapable of fun things like standing. Taking care of bodily needs. For days on end. So I try not to overdo.

So I made a miscalculation. 

Last time I did a fence, I did 40lb bags. This time we have 80lb bags. The posts are the same size. 

...for those of you doing the math at home, yes. Yes, I hauled out 2560 lbs of concrete mix more than I needed today. That exactly. https://t.co/9OFY5Iwnjj
